<TITLE> CA gets two more special aides </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 21 (bdnews24.com)  Two more persons have been appointed to the chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed as special assistants, the Cabinet Division said in a circular Monday, which increases the number of special aides to the CA to five. Soon after, two advisers appointed earlier were given another portfolio each at the same time, the chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told bdnews24.com. One of the two special aides is Singer Bangladesh's chairman and managing director Mahbub Jamil. Jamil is the first special assistant to the CA to be appointed with status of a minister. He has been tasked with civil aviation and tourism, industries, and youth and sports portfolios, Munaim said. The second aide is Manik Lal Samaddar, former secretary to the Implementation Monitoring and Evaluation Division of the planning ministry. Samaddarappointed with status of a state ministerhas been assigned to the fisheries and livestock, and science and information and communication technology ministries. Adviser AF Hassan Ariff has been tasked with the additional land portfolio and adviser Rasheda K Chowdhury with cultural affairs. The government had earlier appointed three other special assistants to the chief adviser. Retired brigadier general MA Malek Mollah had been assigned to the post and telecommunications ministry. Barrister Debashish Roy had been given the portfolio of Chittagong Hill Tracts affairs and Prof M Tamim had been assigned to the energy and mineral resources portfolio. bdnews24.com/
